timeline.bodyText:
Some thoughts here:
It seems that JUnit does not make any guarantees when an Extension is instantiated + there is no explicit closing of the DB connection in this Extension.
I did a little bit of research and from what I was able to tell here's how it's supposed to be done:
Instead of using static fields, the ExtensionContext provides a store to store intermediate values.
This would also allow to make use of the ExtensionContext.Store.CloseableResource interface to do the automated cleanup. Something like
@Override
void beforeAll(ExtensionContext context) {
  context.getStore(ExtensionContext.Namespace.GLOBAL).getOrComputeIfAbsent("JDBI", () -> new JdbiWrapper(/* create jdbi*/), JdbiWrapper .class).getJdbi();;
}

@AllArgsConstructor
@Getter
static class JdbiWrapper implements ExtensionContext.Store.CloseableResource {

  private final Jdbi jdbi;

  @Override
  void close() {
    // cleanup of jdbi
  }
}
Thoughts?

